Michif Genealogical Society Toolbox

A comprehensive suite of Python tools and automated pipelines designed to enhance genealogy research. This toolbox specializes in bulk data conversion, LLM-powered historical document transcription, and direct SQLite database management for RootsMagic and Family Tree Maker.

🛠️ Requirements & Setup

Prerequisites:

Python 3.8+

TamperMonkey (Browser Extension)

Newberry Atlas of Historical County Boundaries – https://publications.newberry.org/ahcb/downloads/gis/US_AtlasHCB_Counties.zip
Extract to a subfolder in the same directory as CountyFix.py.

Installation:
It is highly recommended to use a virtual environment (venv). Install the required dependencies via pip:

pip install pandas geopandas shapely thefuzz python-dotenv tqdm google-genai customtkinter pillow

Install CensusExtractor.js inside your browser's TamperMonkey dashboard.

⚙️ Configuration & The GUI

You con'g need to manually edit .env files if running from the Toolbox (though they have been left in so individual
scripts can still be run from the CLI). Simply launch the main GUI to securely manage all settings, API keys, and
directory paths:

python MGS-Toolbox.py

The GUI automatically generates and updates your local .env file and passes the necessary dynamic variables to the
background scripts. All script outputs and progress bars route directly into the GUI console. (Note: If you prefer
manual setup, refer to the .env.example file in this repository).

🧰 The Utilities

Master GUI (MGS_Toolbox.py): The central hub built with customtkinter. It provides a tabbed interface for global
settings and API budgets, safely manages background subprocesses, and prevents UI freezing during heavy API calls.

Document Extraction & Conversion

Census Extractor (Census/Converter/CensusExtractor.py): Creates transcribed US Census CSVs to use with Census Converter.

Census Converter (CensusConverter/CensusConverter.py): Parses transcribed US Census CSV data into a GEDCOM.
Automatically groups households into family units using complex age/surname heuristics and injects detailed review tasks
for role assignments.

Register Extractor (ChurchRegisters/ChurchGatherData.py): A heavy-duty OCR and translation pipeline utilizing the Gemini
API. It client-side optimizes high-res church registers (LANCZOS resampling) to save tokens, and extracts cursive (
French/Latin) into a structured JSON database using Context Caching.

Register to GEDCOM (ChurchRegisters/ChurchCreateGedcom.py): Compiles the JSON generated by the extractor into a
RootsMagic-optimized GEDCOM 5.5.1 file. Features deterministic MD5-hashed IDs, CAL birthdate calculations, and dynamic
linking for godparents/witnesses via _SHAR tags.

Gemini Cache Cleanup (ChurchRegisters/CacheCleanup.py): A backend maintenance utility that clears all active Gemini
context caches to prevent unnecessary storage costs after batch runs.

Database Management

RootsMagic Duplicate Finder (Dupes/Dupes.py): Scans RootsMagic 11 .rmtree files using fuzzy string matching on names and
birth years. It cross-references immediate family to filter false positives and injects Task/Folder records directly
into the database for native review.

Historical County Fixer (CountyFix/CountyFix.py): Evaluates timeline events against Newberry Atlas shapefiles. If an
event falls outside a county's historical boundaries based on the date, it clones the place record, updates it to the
historically accurate jurisdiction, and redirects the event while preserving UUIDs.

⚠️ CRITICAL: Database Interactions
Dupes.py and CountyFix.py execute direct UPDATE, INSERT, and DELETE SQL operations against proprietary RootsMagic
.rmtree files. RootsMagic does not expect external modifications while running.

Close RootsMagic completely before running these specific scripts.

Always back up your database before execution.

The author provides this toolbox "as is" and assumes no liability for database corruption or data loss.
